AI-based semantic segmentation system using the U-Net architecture with PyTorch. The system takes an image as input and predicts the object class for every pixel in the image . tools and technologies we implemented in this  OpenCV,numpy,matplotlib,googlecolab.
=>system arhitecture.
-> The overall workflow of the system is as follows:
Install required libraries.
Import deep learning and image processing libraries.
Create a U-Net segmentation model.
Prepare dataset and masks.
Train the model using a training loop.
Generate predictions on test images.
Evaluate the segmentation using IoU metric.
Save the trained model.
=>model architecture
project uses the U-Net architecture, which is widely used for semantic segmentation tasks.
U-Net consists of two main parts:
Encoder (Contracting Path)
Extracts features from the input image.
Uses convolution layers and pooling operations.
In our model, the encoder used is ResNet34 pretrained on ImageNet.
Decoder (Expanding Path)
Reconstructs the image segmentation map.
Uses upsampling layers to recover spatial resolution.
Combines low-level and high-level features using skip connections.
=> Dataset Preparation
To train the model, two types of data are required:
Input Images
These are the original images used for training.
Segmentation Masks
A mask is an image where each pixel value represents a class label.
=> In this project:
Images were resized to 256 × 256 pixels
Masks were also resized to 256 × 256 pixels
Images were normalized to improve model performance.
